 are actually available in this environment first. Since we're in May 2026, .NET 11 might still be in preview and may not be installed. Let me try building the project and see what we're working with. Actually, the simplest way to handle the PascalCase conversion without a built-in naming policy would be to either add `[JsonPropertyName]` attributes to each property or use a custom naming policy instead.","outputTokens":1221,"requestId":"A423:1BD058:AD9D5E:D6DE78:6A0128B4"},"id":"d7882263-998c-4837-99cf-3e1994f646ca","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:54:36.383Z","parentId":"be74ef20-4138-492d-80e1-24619be4ef5c"}
